=======
 SNARF 
=======
| 

about
-----
| 

:author:  Wijnand 'tehmaze' Modderman - http://tehmaze.com
:contact: IRCNET/#dunkbots
:distribution: core
:license:  BSD
 
| 

description
-----------
| 

the snarf plugin gets the title of the web page of the provided url or the last url in the log

| 


| 

commands
--------
| 

1) *snarf (title)*

    :description: fetch the title from an URL

    :permissions: USER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !snarf http://gozerbot.org
        <output> gozerbot.org: Gozerbot :: The IRC bot and Jabber bot
        <output>  in one


2) *snarf-cfg*

    :description: plugin configuration

    :permissions: OPER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !snarf-cfg
        <output> options: allow=['text/plain', 'text/html', 'application/xml']
        <output>  .. version="GOZERBOT 0.9"


3) *snarf-cfgsave*

    :description: save plugin configuration

    :permissions: OPER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !snarf-cfgsave
        <output> config saved


4) *snarf-enable (snarf-on)*

    :description: enable snarfing in the channel

    :permissions: OPER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !snarf-enable
        <output> ok


5) *snarf-list*

    :description: show in which channels snarfing is enabled

    :permissions: OPER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !snarf-list
        <output> snarfers enable on: gozerdata: #test


6) *validate (valid)*

    :description: validate an URL

    :permissions: USER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !validate http://gozerbot.org
        <output> gozerbot.org: (unknown) | modified: (undefined) | server:
        <output>  Apache/2.2.8 (Ubuntu) mod_python/3.3.1 Python/2.5.2
        <output>  | size: (undefined) | content-type: text/html | encoding:
        <output>  utf-8 | doctype: XHTML 1.0 Strict


7) *snarf-disable (snarf-off)*

    :description: disable snarfing in the channel

    :permissions: OPER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !snarf-disable
        <output> ok


